    "text": "Erdős Problem #287 [status: falsifiable; formalized: no]. Let $k\\geq 2$. Is it true that, for any distinct integers $1<n_1<\\cdots <n_k$ such that\\[1=\\frac{1}{n_1}+\\cdots+\\frac{1}{n_k}\\]we must have $\\max(n_{i+1}-n_i)\\geq 3$? Current best: The lower bound of $\\geq 2$ is equivalent to saying that $1$ is not the sum of reciprocals of consecutive integers, proved by Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er32}. Prize: no. Tags: number theory, unit fractions.",
